<exercise id="fs-id1167834079569">
<problem id="fs-id1167835519228">
<para id="fs-id1167835519230"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id1167834430029"><media id="fs-id1167835339148" alt="This figure shows the graph of a straight line on the x y-coordinate plane. The x-axis runs from negative 10 to 10. The y-axis runs from negative 10 to 10. The line goes through the points (0, negative 2) and (2, 1).">
